        <num>CCRP 790</num>
        <heading>790.  Swearing of jurors</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 790.  Swearing of jurors
When selection of jurors and alternate jurors has been completed, and all issues properly raised under Article 795 have been resolved, the jurors shall then be sworn together to try the case in a just and impartial manner, each to the best of his judgment, and to render a verdict according to the law and the evidence.</p>
        </content>
